We had such a fun evening of Italian fashion at Cotton Club Collection this week! First, we had our planned Angela Caputi Trunk Show for those jewels that so many people seek out in our town… John Maguire, Co-owner of Cotton Club Collection bought lots of it and almost all was purchased! So if you are an Angela fan, get to Cotton Club quickly. (We’re hopeful that they will buy more soon!!). 

The icing on the cake was a guest appearance by designer Laura Laureto, who was in H-town for the night from Cortona, Italy. Her unique hand-painted luxe leather bags and cashmere wraps were a huge hit with our city’s fashion-savvy gals! The gals that took Tuscany by storm last month with us and @bpptours had a ball and a semi-reunion… and they did of course Shop-till-they-Dropped in Tuscany… the Italian way. Such fun! 🛍

Thanks again to John Maguire & Jennifer Cunningham of @cottonclubcollection, @angelacaputi_giuggiu, and @laura_laureto!

For the first time ever, the Donne Di Domani and University of Houston Department of Italian Language Studies present an exclusive lecture from Dr. Stefania Porcelli.

Have you ever thought about how books and stories can help us understand the environment and climate change? Dr. Stefania Porcelli is doing just that by looking at Elena Ferrante’s popular book My Brilliant Friend. In an exclusive lecture, she will explore how the toxic family relationships in the book are like pollution, affecting not only the city of Naples but spreading to the whole world. Dr. Porcelli hopes to help us pay attention to how books and stories can help us understand and care for the planet we live on.

Elena Ferrante is an award-winning Italian novelist with many of her books turned into series for Netflix and HBO. Dr. Stefania Porcelli is Visiting Assistant Professor at Miami University, Ohio, where she teaches Italian language and culture classes.

Join us at the Italian Cultural & Community Center of Houston (@iccc.houston) for this exciting free event on Monday evening (April 24). Stay after the lecture for wine, soft drinks, and buffet-style appetizers prepared by Amalfi Ristorante Italiano & Bar (@amalfihouston).

You can register at the link in my stories. @donne_di_domani @universityofhouston #elenaferrante #climatechange #bookworm #italianculture #italianlanguage #italianauthor #italianstudies #italianamerican #houstonlife #houstontx #htown

The Met Gala, often considered the fashion world’s equivalent of the Oscars, is an annual event I simply can’t miss.. even if it isn’t universally watched by everyone! This year’s Met Gala was a dazzling homage to legendary fashion icon, Karl Lagerfeld. Celebrities graced the red carpet with timeless Lagerfeld-inspired ensembles and heartfelt, symbolic tributes, evoking a sense of chic elegance. The looks  were a refreshing departure from recent campy and avant-garde themes. 2023’s Gala, “In Honor of Karl,” truly celebrated the essence of fashion. Head to the blog to read more and see all of my favorite looks!

#karllagerfeld #metgala #celebrityfashion #redcarpet #houstonfashion #houstonstyle #houstonblogger

I had an incredible time stepping into the heart of Jewish deli culture at the newest exhibit at the Holocaust Museum, “I’ll Have What She’s Having.” Named after the iconic line from “When Harry Met Sally,” this exhibit tells the story of the Jewish deli and its impact on American culture. Hosted by none other than Houston’s own “Deli-man” Ziggy Gruber, it was an incredible blend of history, nostalgia, and of course, delicious food. This immersive experience of Jewish immigration, cuisine, and culture is a testament to the enduring legacy of these beloved institutions. From the iconic dishes to personal memorabilia, don’t miss this savory slice of American history!!

@hmhou @kennyandziggys @ziggy_gruber #ziggygruber #jewishdeli #delicatessen #houstoneats #houstonfood #houstontx

Have you been to BARI❓Bari Ristorante Italiano in Houston's River Oaks District has quickly become a go-to spot for fine Italian dining! 

It’s hard to put into words the high-energy, bustling yet still warm vibe that I felt the moment I walked in… Tommy Nally and Pedro Teyuca, the experienced restauranteurs behind Bari Ristorante, have created an amazing dining experience. Chef Renatto DePiro, with 30 years of culinary expertise, has created a menu of classic Italian dishes with a modern twist. If you’re a fan of homemade pasta, hand-tossed pizza, or refreshing apertivos, you’ll love a night at Bari. 

Bari Ristorante is a must-visit addition to Houston's fine dining scene and I look forward to my next visit. Read more about my experience and see additional images in my stories and on the blog!
